  "title": "Re-Equip",
  "description": "Version 1.21.1 | Exploration, Looting, Weapon & Tool Upgrades | Vanilla+",
  "body": "![About](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/cached_images/4e39b69d8c51a933a16fb67d9d76737dd9cfc90f_0.webp)\n\nAs the name already suggests, it is somewhat about Equipment. There are plenty of mods in this pack that add new ways of getting weapons, tools or even new items such as artifacts and relics. The World-Generation is still vanilla-like with the addition of new structures and mobs but in a balanced way. The Modpack is supposed to be played in a casual way but you can also take a deeper dive into some mods or step up the difficulty. However you decide to play the game, it's best with friends!\n\n### Features\n- New structures with [Explorify](https://modrinth.com/datapack/explorify), [YUNG's Structure-Suite](https://modrinth.com/user/YUNGNICKYOUNG) and more\n- New ways to get or upgrade tools/weapons with [Apotheosis](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/apotheosis)\n- Better exploration with [Antique Atlas 4](https://modrinth.com/mod/antique-atlas-4) and [Wraith's Waystones](https://modrinth.com/mod/fwaystones)\n- Overhauled Nether with [Amplified Nether](https://modrinth.com/datapack/amplified-nether) and [Nether Weather](https://modrinth.com/datapack/netherweather)\n- Better Performance for Clients and Servers with [Sodium](https://modrinth.com/mod/sodium) and [Lithium](https://modrinth.com/mod/lithium)\n- Quick and easy multiplayer setup with [e4mc](https://modrinth.com/mod/e4mc)\n- And of course a lot of QoL and immersive Additions\n\n### Notes\n- The Modpack autoloads Datapacks and Ressourcepacks via [Paxi](https://modrinth.com/mod/paxi), which can be changed in Re-Equip\\config\\paxi.\n- When using e4mc for multiplayer, it might come to connection-issues, based on traffic in your own network. For instance another device in your network, which is using a streaming service, will influence the server-performance. For more information check [e4mc-minecraft-architectury](https://github.com/vgskye/e4mc-minecraft-architectury).\n- Keybind-Conflicts are initially not resolved.\n\n### IMPORTANT\nIt is recommended to disable or remove [Vanilla Refresh](https://modrinth.com/datapack/vanilla-refresh) and [Spawn Animations](https://modrinth.com/datapack/spawn-animations) to get a better multiplayer-experience, since these datapacks/mods cause a lot of lag.\n\n<details>\n  <summary>Mods, Datapacks and Shader</summary>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/entity-model-features\">\n          [EMF] Entity Model Feature\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/entitytexturefeatures\">\n          [ETF] Entity Texture Features\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/accelerated-decay\">\n          Accelerated Decay\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/advancement-plaques\">\n          Advancement Plaques\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/ai-improvements\">\n          AI Improvements\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/ambientsounds\">\n          Ambient Sounds\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/amendments\">\n          Amendments\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/datapack/amplified-nether\">\n          Amplified Nether\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/antique-atlas-4\">\n          Antique Atlas 4\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/apotheosis\">\n          Apotheosis\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/apothic-attributes\">\n          Apothic Attributes\n        </a>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/apothic-combat\">\n          Apothic Combat\n        </a>\n     